The question is asking to find the minimum no of operation to reach 1 either by dividing 6 (only if completely divisible) or by multiplying by 2 
first of all if n == 1 it means no operation is required so we simply return 0 
now to reach 1, we have two options either multiply by 2 means we are increasing pow of 2 right or if we divide by 6 it removes one 2 and one 3 so to reach 1 we must remove all powers
So to remove all 3s, we must have enough 2s available. if too many 2s -> no way to remove extra ones in that case we'll cout (-1).
Because multiply-by-2 only increases 2s.
so we'll maintain cnt2, cnt3 if cnt2 > cnt3 it we need more 2s so we multiply 2 by (cnt3 - cnt2) times now powers are equal so operation needed = (cnt3 - cnt2)
now to remove pow by /6 we need cnt3 operations so total operations = (cnt3 - cnt2) + cnt3

